==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inclusa
<hw>In*clu"sa</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. L.
<ets>inclusus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>includere</ets> to shut in.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A tribe of bivalve mollusks, characterized by
the closed state of the mantle which envelops the body. The ship borer
(<spn>Teredo navalis</spn>) is an example.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inclusion</ent>⟦br⟧
